properties.documentation: Not described in the SWE Common standard. This structure is derived from the swe:EncodedValuesPropertyType in the SWE Common XML Schema.

Source SWE Common The DataChoice class (also called Disjoint Union) is modeled on the definition of Choice from ISO 11404. It is a composite component that allows for a choice of child components. By opposition to records that carry all their fields simultaneously, only one item at a time can be present in the data when wrapped in a DataChoice.
